# Inngest & Background Job Conventions

## Architecture
- Inngest client is a singleton in `src/lib/inngest/client.ts` (id: `"fanzy"`)
- All Inngest functions live in `src/lib/inngest/functions/`
- Functions are registered and served via `src/app/api/inngest/route.ts`
- The serve route exposes `GET`, `POST`, `PUT` methods — do not add middleware that blocks these

## Event Naming
- Format: `domain/resource.action` (e.g. `project/generation.requested`, `scene/video.completed`)
- Define event types using `eventType()` with `staticSchema<T>()` for type safety
- Event data should contain IDs (not full objects) plus the minimum data needed for execution

## Function Pattern
- One function per job type
- Use `step.run("step-name", async () => { ... })` for each atomic operation
- Use `step.sleep("wait-name", duration)` for polling intervals
- Step names must be unique within a function — use descriptive suffixes

## Retries & Timeouts
- Default retries: 2 (configured in function options)
- Polling intervals: 5s for short jobs, configurable for long-running video generation
- If polling exhausts attempts, mark the job as `FAILED`

## Forbidden
- Don't import Inngest client outside of `src/lib/inngest/` and the serve route
- Don't call Inngest functions directly — always send events via `inngest.send()`
- Don't put UI or React code in Inngest function files
